          MODULE=makedev
         VERSION=1.4.2
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$MODULE-$VERSION
         ENTERED=20020319
         UPDATED=20020526
           SHORT="makedev (MAKEDEV) is a script to (re-)create the devices under /dev"
cat << EOF
makedev (MAKEDEV) is a script to (re-)create the devices under /dev
Usage:
to create the devices try ./MAKEDEV generic as root while you are in /dev
to update the devices try ./MAKEDEV update
use parameter -v for verbose and -n for dry run
use -V parameter for version info
without any parameters, the script does nothing
EOF
